-- Mexico Stocks: America Movil, Elektra, Modelo, Walmex Decline
-- B y   J o n a t h a n   J .   L e v i n
-- 2012-01-24T19:35:49Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-01-24/mexico-stocks-america-movil-elektra-modelo-walmex-decline.html
The following companies are having
unusual price changes in  Mexico  trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses and prices are as of 12:57 p.m. Mexico City time.  The IPC  index  fell 0.9 percent to 36,872.11.  Mexican stocks followed U.S. equities lower amid a
stalemate between European finance ministers and Greek
bondholders over how to resolve the nation’s debt crisis.  Grupo Modelo SA (GMODELOC)  , Mexico’s largest beer maker,
fell 1.6 percent to 80.98 pesos.  Wal-Mart de Mexico SAB  (WALMEXV
MM), Latin America’s largest retailer, declined 1.2 percent to
37.95 pesos.  America Movil SAB (AMXL)  , the wireless carrier
controlled by billionaire  Carlos Slim , dropped 1.2 percent to
15.12 pesos.  Grupo Elektra SA (ELEKTRA*)  , the retail and banking
company controlled by billionaire  Ricardo Salinas , tumbled 6.4
percent to 1,107 pesos. Investors are taking profits after
Elektra more than doubled in price in the past year, Juan Jose
Gutierrez, an analyst with Bursametrica SA in Mexico City, said
in a telephone interview from Mexico City.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Jonathan J. Levin in Mexico City at 
